rest_of_day_open:
My week will go in much the same vein as it typically has, though I do actually feel a little more uplifted about it. Being connected with a new person, even via the limitations of a video-chat makes me happy the way that extroverts and ambiverts get.

I believe that I might actually find it easier to deal with the guests at work more peaceably, though that might just be wishful thinking. He was very kind and I wish to pass that forward.
critical_positive: The conversation worked well when I took lead and directed the conversation; having specific topics helped to ease my partner's nervousness with speaking to a stranger. Using a bit of humour also assisted in breaking the ice between us; common ground found in the COVID-19 crisis was also useful for this.
critical_negative: I needed to give him more time to collect and frame his thoughts, to speak out so I wasn't talking over him. This happens a lot with video-chats more so than in face-to-face meetings.  There was also a distinct lack of body-language that couldn't help in the interpretation of tone or intent, which didn't work well at some points (I have a sharp voice and manner).

rest_of_day_open: I imagine it will be pretty similar to how my weeks usually go. Even though it's the Memorial Day weekend, there's still some anxiety in my area about the coronavirus situation, and I'm in a state that has proven to be very cautious. I think it will just be spent at home with a lot of Zoom calls (which isn't bad, necessarily, just more of the same).
critical_positive: I was tired going into this since it started at 6:45 a.m., so I allowed my conversation partner to talk for most of the time. I think that worked really well because my brain wasn't exactly high-functioning for a good chunk of the conversation. I also could read our dynamic and knew that my partner was definitely the more talkative one.
critical_negative: I think I made an initial first impression about my partner based on various factors, such as how they looked and how they sounded, and I think that influenced my view of what kind of person they were in a negative way. That probably made me more apprehensive and guarded during the conversation.
